SIMPLE: mudsill
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mudsill
<hw>Mud"sill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
lowest sill of a structure, usually embedded in the soil; the lowest
timber of a house; also, that sill or timber of a bridge which is laid
at the bottom of the water. See <er>Sill</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: A person of the lowest stratum of society; --
a term of opprobrium or contempt.</def> <mark>[Southern U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mudsucker</ent>⟦br⟧
